<p>where <b>W</b> is a <i>p</i>-by-<i>p</i> matrix of weights whose columns=
 are the eigenvectors of <b>X</b><sup>T</sup><b>X</b>. The transpose of <b>=
W</b> is sometimes called the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whit=
ening_transformation" title=3D"Whitening transformation">whitening or spher=
ing transformation</a>. Columns of <b>W</b> multiplied by the square root o=
f corresponding eigenvalues, that is, eigenvectors scaled up by the varianc=
es, are called <i>loadings</i> in PCA or in Factor analysis.
</p>
