tsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Independent_component_analy=
sis">Independent component analysis</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/w/index.php?title=3DPrincipal_component_analysis&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;=
section=3D42" title=3D"Edit section: Independent component analysis"><span>=
edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independent_component_analysis"=
 title=3D"Independent component analysis">Independent component analysis</a=
> (ICA) is directed to similar problems as principal component analysis, bu=
t finds additively separable components rather than successive approximatio=
ns.
</p>
